{
  "id": "medium_06_ts",
  "title": "Counter Closure (TS)",
  "difficulty": "medium",
  "category": "nonlocal + unimplemented closure",
  "description": "Implement a stateful counter using closures. Given a sequence of operations and a starting value, apply each operation in order and return the list of counter values after each step.\n\nSupported operations:\n- `\"inc\"` — add `amount` to the counter, return the new value.\n- `\"dec\"` — subtract `amount` from the counter, return the new value.\n\n**Example 1:**\nInput: `operations = [[\"inc\", 1], [\"inc\", 2], [\"inc\", 3]], start = 0`\nOutput: `[1, 3, 6]`\nExplanation: 0+1=1, 1+2=3, 3+3=6\n\n**Example 2:**\nInput: `operations = [[\"inc\", 5], [\"dec\", 2]], start = 0`\nOutput: `[5, 3]`\n\n**Example 3:**\nInput: `operations = [[\"inc\", 1]], start = 10`\nOutput: `[11]`\n\n**Constraints:**\n- `1 <= len(operations) <= 100`\n- `op ∈ {\"inc\", \"dec\"}`\n- `0 <= amount <= 1000`\n- `-10000 <= start <= 10000`\n\n**Tasks:** `increment` throws an error on the first call — check how `count` is declared and whether that allows reassignment inside a closure. Also implement `decrement` in `counter.js`.",
  "files": [
    {
      "name": "counter.ts",
      "editable": true
    },
    {
      "name": "main.ts",
      "editable": true
    }
  ],
  "entry_module": "main",
  "entry_function": "runOperations",
  "test_cases": [
    {
      "args": [
        [
          [
            "inc",
            1
          ],
          [
            "inc",
            2
          ],
          [
            "inc",
            3
          ]
        ],
        0
      ],
      "expected": [
        1,
        3,
        6
      ]
    },
